---
import ServicePage from '../../components/ServicePage.astro';
---
<ServicePage
	title="in Clapham"
	highlight="Vojta Therapy"
	heroSubtitle="A specialised neurological treatment that activates innate movement patterns within the central nervous system."
	breadcrumb="Vojta Therapy"
	seoTitle="Vojta Therapy in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Vojta Therapy in Clapham for infants, children, and adults. A reflex-based neurological treatment supporting posture, coordination, and mobility."
	intro={[
		"Movement problems linked to the nervous system can affect how the body develops, adapts, and functions day to day. Vojta Therapy is a specialised neurological treatment that works by activating innate movement patterns within the central nervous system.",
		"Rather than relying on voluntary effort alone, it stimulates automatic responses that underpin posture, coordination, and mobility.",
		"Treatment is delivered by trained therapists and is suitable for infants, children, and adults with a range of neurological and movement conditions.",
	]}
	whenHeading="When to consider"
	whenHighlight="Vojta Therapy"
	whenList={[
		"Delays in motor development such as rolling, crawling, or walking",
		"Difficulties with coordination, posture, or muscle tone",
		"Asymmetrical movement or a preference for one side",
		"Spasticity or stiffness affecting fluid movement",
		"Neurological conditions such as cerebral palsy",
		"Movement limitations following stroke or brain injury",
	]}
	howHeading="How we"
	howHighlight="treat"
	howList={[
		"Targeted stimulation of reflex points to activate global movement patterns",
		"Positioning to support postural control and alignment",
		"Guidance for home-based therapy where appropriate",
		"Ongoing reassessment of movement quality and control",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Infants and children with developmental delays or neurological conditions",
		"Children with cerebral palsy or motor control disorders",
		"Adults recovering from stroke or neurological injury",
		"Individuals with complex movement disorders",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "What is Vojta Therapy?", a: "A neurological rehabilitation method using reflex locomotion to activate automatic movement patterns." },
		{ q: "Is it only for children?", a: "No. It is effective for adults with neurological conditions too." },
		{ q: "How is it different from other therapies?", a: "It focuses on activating involuntary, reflex-driven patterns rather than voluntary movement alone." },
		{ q: "Will my child cry during treatment?", a: "Some children may cry due to the effort involved, not typically because of pain." },
		{ q: "How many sessions will we need?", a: "This varies individually; a structured plan is provided after the initial assessment." },
		{ q: "Do I need a referral?", a: "No direct referral is required." },
	]}
/>
